Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga is confident all schools are ready for full-time classes. Cabinet ended rotational learning earlier this week. Social distancing of one metre for pupils will also no longer be applicable. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga is confident all schools are ready for full-time classes. Cabinet ended rotational learning earlier this week. WATCH | Minister Motshekga briefs media on school readiness One metre of social distancing for pupils will also no longer be applicable. Motshekga says a number of concerns were raised before rotational learning was stopped. Schools across the country will be returning to full attendance from Monday. Motshekga is also urging all teachers and eligible pupils to get their COVID-19 jab.